ratings.question_text: How responsive to student comments was the instructor?
I would give the instructor of this class an overall rating of:
I would give this course an overall rating of:
Apart from how well the course was taught, how valuable is the course to students with interests similar to yours?
Did you participate in a work group as part of this course?

narratives.question_text: Use the space below to comment on questions 1-10, if you wish
comments: This "class" is a joke. I understand why Yale requires it, but the material could have been presented much more succinctly and in a much more relevant way if it was combined with the first semester doctoral seminar.Further, having the class on 3 Friday mornings meant that half of us either had to leave this class early or miss other classes because of the conflict. Better scheduling is a must.

narratives.question_text: The things about this course most in need of improvement are:
comments: The examples are canned and cheesy and so completely not applicable to real life.

narratives.question_text: What was the availability and quality of help you received of the instructor and TA?
Discuss if you wish how this course fits into your overall program.
comments: Just a requirement. Not helpful at all.
Fits well with first year PhD program. Could be incorporated into a research methods class.

narratives.question_text: Why did you take this course?

comments: Better than expected. I am not sure it is the right format though.
